When it is pointed out that Paul engaged in fundraising activities in Phillippians 4, some respond by saying something like this:
&ldquo;Paul was not accepting a &ldquo;seed money&rdquo; for blessing like the TV preachers. He was just accepting small gifts for his own personal needs. It was not something that could be called &lsquo;fund raising&rsquo;.&rdquo;
Paul seemed to be taking up a collection for &ldquo;the poor&rdquo; in Jerusalem as we see in Romans 15:25-26.
